- Intall Postgresql contrib package

    sudo apt-get install postrgresql-contrib

- Enable the uuid-ossp contrib module in a database (you need superuser permissions)

    # log into psql as superuser

    $ psql
    mike=#

    # change to the desired database

    mike# \c mydb 
    You are now connected to "mydb" as user "mike".
    mydb=#

    # enable uuid-ossp (note the double quotes)
    
    mydb=# CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "uuid-ossp";
    CREATE EXTENSION

    # you can now logout from your superuser account and log back in as a normal user.

- Generating a uuid4

    mydb=> select uuid_generate_v4();

- Inserting a row with a uuid field 

    mydb=> INSERT INTO mytable (my_id) \
           VALUES (uuid_generate_v4());

- selecting uuid

    SELECT * FROM accounts WHERE account_id::text ILIKE '22c5%';
    DELETE FROM products WHERE product_id::text ILIKE 'b3a8%';
